               <msContents>
                  <summary>Business letter from the Arsinoite Nome (modern name: Fayyum), Egypt. Written to someone with "anias" in his name. Concerns the purchase of a house from(?) the wife of Didymos. The writer himself is on his way to the town of Pelousion. Dated to Epeiph 7, year 17 (July 19, 97 B.C.)</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Actual dimensions of item are 20.7 x 16.4 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">15 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers on the recto; the address written along the fibers on the verso in large letters</note>
                     <note type="general">Lower margin of 5.5 cm.; left margin of 2.5 cm.; small right margin</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 97 was formerly P.Rob.inv. 2</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
